text: Libyans in the US celebrate Moammar Gadhafi's death.
President Barack Obama says Gadhafi's death is a warning to dictators.
The U.S. Senate votes against President Barack Obama's jobs bill for the second time in less than two weeks.
Secretary of State Hillary Clinton holds a news conference in Islamabad with the Pakistani Foreign Minister.
A mild earthquake hit the small city of Pleasanton, Texas.
